{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"Because of what I'm about to say,"},{"time":2000,"text":"I really should establish my green credentials."},{"time":5000,"text":"When I was a small boy, I took my pledge"},{"time":7000,"text":"as an American, to save and faithfully defend from waste"},{"time":10000,"text":"the natural resources of my country,"},{"time":12000,"text":"its air, soil and minerals, its forests, waters and wildlife."},{"time":15000,"text":"And I've stuck to that."},{"time":17000,"text":"Stanford, I majored in ecology and evolution."},{"time":21000,"text":"1968, I put out the Whole Earth Catalog. Was \"mister natural\" for a while."}]},{"cues":[{"time":25000,"text":"And then worked for the Jerry Brown administration."},{"time":28000,"text":"The Brown administration, and a bunch of my friends,"},{"time":31000,"text":"basically leveled the energy efficiency of California,"},{"time":34000,"text":"so it's the same now, 30 years later,"},{"time":37000,"text":"even though our economy has gone up 80 percent, per capita."},{"time":41000,"text":"And we are putting out less greenhouse gasses than any other state."},{"time":44000,"text":"California is basically the equivalent of Europe, in this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":47000,"text":"This year, Whole Earth Catalog has a supplement that I'll preview today,"},{"time":52000,"text":"called Whole Earth Discipline."},{"time":55000,"text":"The dominant demographic event of our time"},{"time":57000,"text":"is this screamingly rapid urbanization"},{"time":60000,"text":"that we have going on."},{"time":62000,"text":"By mid-century we'll be about 80 percent urban,"},{"time":66000,"text":"and that's mostly in the developing world,"},{"time":69000,"text":"where that's happening."},{"time":71000,"text":"It's interesting, because history is driven to a large degree"},{"time":74000,"text":"by the size of cities."},{"time":76000,"text":"The developing world now has all of the biggest cities,"},{"time":79000,"text":"and they are developing three times faster than the developed countries,"},{"time":82000,"text":"and nine times bigger."},{"time":84000,"text":"It's qualitatively different."},{"time":87000,"text":"They are the drivers of history, as we see by looking at history."}]},{"cues":[{"time":89000,"text":"1,000 years ago this is what the world looked like."},{"time":93000,"text":"Well we now have a distribution of urban power"},{"time":96000,"text":"similar to what we had 1,000 years ago."},{"time":99000,"text":"In other words, the rise of the West,"},{"time":101000,"text":"dramatic as it was, is over."},{"time":105000,"text":"The aggregate numbers are absolutely overwhelming:"},{"time":108000,"text":"1.3 million people a week coming to town,"},{"time":111000,"text":"decade after decade."},{"time":113000,"text":"What's really going on?"},{"time":115000,"text":"Well, what's going on is the villages of the world are emptying out."},{"time":118000,"text":"Subsistence farming is drying up basically."}]},{"cues":[{"time":121000,"text":"People are following opportunity into town."},{"time":123000,"text":"And this is why."},{"time":125000,"text":"I used to have a very romantic idea about villages,"},{"time":127000,"text":"and it's because I never lived in one."},{"time":130000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":131000,"text":"Because in town --"},{"time":133000,"text":"this is the bustling squatter city"},{"time":135000,"text":"of Kibera, near Nairobi --"},{"time":139000,"text":"they see action. They see opportunity."},{"time":141000,"text":"They see a cash economy that they were not able to participate in"},{"time":144000,"text":"back in the subsistence farm."}]},{"cues":[{"time":147000,"text":"As you go around these places there's plenty of aesthetics."},{"time":149000,"text":"There is plenty going on."},{"time":151000,"text":"They are poor, but they are intensely urban. And they are intensely creative."},{"time":155000,"text":"The aggregate numbers now"},{"time":157000,"text":"are that basically squatters,"},{"time":160000,"text":"all one billion of them, are building the urban world,"},{"time":163000,"text":"which means they're building the world --"},{"time":166000,"text":"personally, one by one, family by family,"},{"time":168000,"text":"clan by clan, neighborhood by neighborhood."},{"time":171000,"text":"They start flimsy and they get substantial as time goes by."},{"time":175000,"text":"They even build their own infrastructure."},{"time":177000,"text":"Well, steal their own infrastructure, at first."},{"time":180000,"text":"Cable TV, water, the whole gamut, all gets stolen."},{"time":183000,"text":"And then gradually gentrifies."}]},{"cues":[{"time":187000,"text":"It is not the case that slums undermine prosperity,"},{"time":190000,"text":"not the working slums; they help create prosperity."},{"time":194000,"text":"So in a town like Mumbai, which is half slums,"},{"time":197000,"text":"it's 1/6th of the GDP of India."},{"time":200000,"text":"Social capital in the slums is at its most urban and dense."},{"time":205000,"text":"These people are valuable as a group."},{"time":208000,"text":"And that's how they work."}]},{"cues":[{"time":210000,"text":"There is a lot of people who think about all these poor people,"},{"time":213000,"text":"\"Oh there's terrible things. We've got to fix their housing.\""},{"time":215000,"text":"It used to be, \"Oh we've got to get them phone service.\""},{"time":217000,"text":"Now they're showing us how they do their phone service."},{"time":220000,"text":"Famine mostly is a rural event now."},{"time":222000,"text":"There are things they care about."},{"time":224000,"text":"And this is where we can help."},{"time":227000,"text":"And the nations they're in can help."},{"time":229000,"text":"And they are helping each other solve these issues."}]},{"cues":[{"time":232000,"text":"And you go to a nice dense place like this slum in Mumbai."},{"time":236000,"text":"You look at that lane on the right."},{"time":238000,"text":"And you can ask, \"Okay what's going on there?\""},{"time":240000,"text":"The answer is, \"Everything.\""},{"time":243000,"text":"This is better than a mall. It's much denser."},{"time":246000,"text":"It's much more interactive."},{"time":248000,"text":"And the scale is terrific."},{"time":250000,"text":"The main event is, these are not people crushed by poverty."},{"time":254000,"text":"These are people busy getting out of poverty"},{"time":256000,"text":"just as fast as they can."},{"time":258000,"text":"They're helping each other do it."},{"time":260000,"text":"They're doing it through an outlaw thing,"},{"time":262000,"text":"the informal economy."},{"time":264000,"text":"The informal economy, it's sort of like dark energy in astrophysics:"},{"time":268000,"text":"it's not supposed to be there, but it's huge."},{"time":270000,"text":"We don't understand how it works yet, but we have to."}]},{"cues":[{"time":273000,"text":"Furthermore, people in the informal economy,"},{"time":275000,"text":"the gray economy --"},{"time":277000,"text":"as time goes by,"},{"time":279000,"text":"crime is happening around them. And they can join the criminal world,"},{"time":283000,"text":"or they can join the legitimate world."},{"time":287000,"text":"We should be able to make that choice"},{"time":289000,"text":"easier for them to get toward the legitimate world,"},{"time":291000,"text":"because if we don't, they will go toward the criminal world."},{"time":295000,"text":"There's all kinds of activity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":298000,"text":"In Dharavi the slum performs not only"},{"time":300000,"text":"a lot of services for itself,"},{"time":302000,"text":"but it performs services for the city at large."},{"time":305000,"text":"And one of the main events are these ad-hoc schools."},{"time":308000,"text":"Parents pool their money to hire some local teachers"},{"time":312000,"text":"to a private, tiny, unofficial school."},{"time":314000,"text":"Education is more possible in the cities, and that changes the world."},{"time":319000,"text":"So you see some interesting, typical, urban things."}]},{"cues":[{"time":322000,"text":"So one thing slammed up against another,"},{"time":324000,"text":"such as in Sao Paulo here."},{"time":326000,"text":"That's what cities do. That's how they create value,"},{"time":328000,"text":"is by slamming things together."},{"time":330000,"text":"In this case, supply right next to demand."},{"time":332000,"text":"So the maids and the gardeners and the guards"},{"time":334000,"text":"that live in this lively part of town on the left"},{"time":337000,"text":"walk to work, in the boring, rich neighborhood."}]},{"cues":[{"time":342000,"text":"Proximity is amazing."},{"time":345000,"text":"We are learning about how dense proximity can be."},{"time":360000,"text":"Connectivity between the city and the country"},{"time":363000,"text":"is what's going to keep the country good,"},{"time":366000,"text":"because the city has interesting ways of doing things."},{"time":378000,"text":"This is what makes cities --"},{"time":380000,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":384000,"text":"this is what makes cities so green in the developing world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":387000,"text":"Because people leave the poverty trap, an ecological disaster"},{"time":390000,"text":"of subsistence farms, and head to town."},{"time":393000,"text":"And when they're gone the natural environment"},{"time":395000,"text":"starts to come back very rapidly."},{"time":397000,"text":"And those who remain in the village can shift over to cash crops"},{"time":400000,"text":"to send food to the new growing markets in town."},{"time":404000,"text":"So if you want to save a village, you do it with a good road,"},{"time":407000,"text":"or with a good cell phone connection, and ideally some grid electrical power."}]},{"cues":[{"time":411000,"text":"So the event is: we're a city planet. That just happened."},{"time":414000,"text":"More than half."},{"time":416000,"text":"The numbers are considerable. A billion live in the squatter cities now."},{"time":419000,"text":"Another billion is expected."},{"time":422000,"text":"That's more than a sixth of humanity living a certain way."},{"time":425000,"text":"And that will determine a lot of how we function."}]},{"cues":[{"time":429000,"text":"Now, for us environmentalists,"},{"time":431000,"text":"maybe the greenest thing about the cities is they diffuse the population bomb."},{"time":434000,"text":"People get into town."},{"time":437000,"text":"The immediately have fewer children."},{"time":439000,"text":"They don't even have to get rich yet. Just the opportunity of"},{"time":442000,"text":"coming up in the world means they will have fewer, higher-quality kids,"},{"time":446000,"text":"and the birthrate goes down radically."}]},{"cues":[{"time":448000,"text":"Very interesting side effect here,"},{"time":450000,"text":"here's a slide from Phillip Longman."},{"time":452000,"text":"Shows what is happening."},{"time":454000,"text":"As we have more and more old people, like me,"},{"time":456000,"text":"and fewer and fewer babies."},{"time":458000,"text":"And they are regionally separated."},{"time":461000,"text":"What you're getting is a world which is"},{"time":463000,"text":"old folks, and old cities, going around doing things the old way,"},{"time":468000,"text":"in the north."},{"time":470000,"text":"And young people in brand new cities they're inventing,"},{"time":473000,"text":"doing new things, in the south."},{"time":475000,"text":"Where do you think the action is going to be?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":478000,"text":"Shift of subject. Quickly drop by climate."},{"time":481000,"text":"The climate news, I'm sorry to say, is going to keep getting worse"},{"time":483000,"text":"than we think, faster than we think."},{"time":486000,"text":"Climate is a profoundly complex, nonlinear system,"},{"time":488000,"text":"full of runaway positive feedbacks,"},{"time":491000,"text":"hidden thresholds and irrevocable tipping points."},{"time":493000,"text":"Here's just a few samples."},{"time":496000,"text":"We're going to keep being surprised. And almost all"},{"time":498000,"text":"the surprises are going to be bad ones."}]},{"cues":[{"time":500000,"text":"From your standpoint this means"},{"time":503000,"text":"a great increase in climate refugees"},{"time":505000,"text":"over the coming decades,"},{"time":507000,"text":"and what goes along with that, which is resource wars"},{"time":510000,"text":"and chaos wars,"},{"time":512000,"text":"as we're seeing in Darfur."},{"time":519000,"text":"That's what drought does."},{"time":521000,"text":"It brings carrying capacity down,"},{"time":523000,"text":"and there's not enough carrying capacity"},{"time":525000,"text":"to support the people. And then you're in trouble."}]},{"cues":[{"time":528000,"text":"Shift to the power situation."},{"time":531000,"text":"Baseload electricity is what it takes to run a city,"},{"time":534000,"text":"or a city planet."},{"time":536000,"text":"So far there is only three sources of baseload electricity:"},{"time":540000,"text":"coal, some gas,"},{"time":543000,"text":"nuclear and hydro."},{"time":545000,"text":"Of those, only nuclear and hydro are green."},{"time":549000,"text":"Coal is what is causing the climate problems."},{"time":551000,"text":"And everyone will keep burning it"},{"time":553000,"text":"because it's so cheap, until governments make it expensive."},{"time":556000,"text":"Wind and solar can't help, because so far we don't have a way to store that energy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":561000,"text":"So with hydro maxed out,"},{"time":564000,"text":"coal and lose the climate,"},{"time":567000,"text":"or nuclear, which is the current operating low-carbon source,"},{"time":570000,"text":"and maybe save the climate."},{"time":572000,"text":"And if we can eventually get good solar in space,"},{"time":575000,"text":"that also could help."},{"time":577000,"text":"Because remember, this is what drives the prosperity in the developing world"},{"time":582000,"text":"in the villages and in the cities."}]},{"cues":[{"time":585000,"text":"So, between coal and nuclear,"},{"time":587000,"text":"compare their waste products."},{"time":589000,"text":"If all of the electricity you used in your lifetime was nuclear,"},{"time":593000,"text":"the amount of waste that would be added up"},{"time":595000,"text":"would fit in a Coke can."},{"time":598000,"text":"Whereas a coal-burning plant,"},{"time":600000,"text":"a normal one gigawatt coal plant, burns 80 rail cars of coal a day,"},{"time":604000,"text":"each car having 100 tons."},{"time":607000,"text":"And it puts 18 thousand tons"},{"time":609000,"text":"of carbon dioxide in the air."},{"time":613000,"text":"So and then when you compare the lifetime emissions"},{"time":615000,"text":"of these various energy forms,"},{"time":617000,"text":"nuclear is about even with solar and wind,"},{"time":619000,"text":"and ahead of solar --"},{"time":621000,"text":"oh, I'm sorry -- with hydro and wind, and ahead of solar."}]},{"cues":[{"time":624000,"text":"And does nuclear really compete with coal?"},{"time":626000,"text":"Just ask the coal miners in Australia."},{"time":628000,"text":"That's where you see some of the source,"},{"time":630000,"text":"not from my fellow environmentalists,"},{"time":632000,"text":"but from people who feel threatened by nuclear power."},{"time":635000,"text":"Well the good news is that"},{"time":637000,"text":"the developing world, but frankly, the whole world,"},{"time":639000,"text":"is busy building, and starting to build, nuclear reactors."},{"time":643000,"text":"This is good for the atmosphere."},{"time":645000,"text":"It's good for their prosperity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":647000,"text":"I want to point out one interesting thing,"},{"time":649000,"text":"which is that environmentalists like the thing we call micropower."},{"time":652000,"text":"It's supposed to be, I don't know, local solar and wind and cogeneration,"},{"time":655000,"text":"and good things like that."},{"time":657000,"text":"But frankly micro-reactors which are just now coming on,"},{"time":659000,"text":"might serve even better."}]},{"cues":[{"time":661000,"text":"The Russians, who started this, are building floating reactors,"},{"time":663000,"text":"for their new passage, where the ice is melting, north of Russia."},{"time":667000,"text":"And they're selling these floating reactors,"},{"time":670000,"text":"only 35 megawatts, to developing countries."},{"time":674000,"text":"Here's the design of an early one from Toshiba."},{"time":676000,"text":"It's interesting, say, to take a 25-megawatt,"},{"time":679000,"text":"25 million watts,"},{"time":681000,"text":"and you compare it to the standard big iron"},{"time":683000,"text":"of an ordinary Westinghouse or Ariva,"},{"time":687000,"text":"which is 1.2, 1.6 billion watts."},{"time":690000,"text":"These things are way smaller. They're much more adaptable."},{"time":694000,"text":"Here's an American design from Lawrence Livermore Lab."},{"time":697000,"text":"Here's another American design that came out"},{"time":699000,"text":"of Los Alamos, and is now commercial."}]},{"cues":[{"time":702000,"text":"Almost all of these are not only small, they are proliferation-proof."},{"time":704000,"text":"They're typically buried in the ground."},{"time":707000,"text":"And the innovation is moving very rapidly."},{"time":709000,"text":"So I think microreactors is going to be important for the future."},{"time":712000,"text":"In terms of proliferation,"},{"time":714000,"text":"nuclear energy has done more"},{"time":716000,"text":"to dismantle nuclear weapons than any other activity."},{"time":719000,"text":"And that's why 10 percent of the electricity in this room,"},{"time":723000,"text":"20 percent of electricity"},{"time":725000,"text":"in this room is probably nuclear."},{"time":727000,"text":"Half of that is coming from dismantled warheads from Russia,"},{"time":731000,"text":"soon to be joined by our dismantled warheads."},{"time":734000,"text":"And so I would like to see the GNEP program,"},{"time":737000,"text":"that was developed in the Bush administration, go forward aggressively."},{"time":740000,"text":"And I was glad to see that president Obama"},{"time":742000,"text":"supported the nuclear fuel bank strategy"},{"time":745000,"text":"when he spoke in Prague the other week."}]},{"cues":[{"time":747000,"text":"One more subject. Genetically engineered food crops,"},{"time":750000,"text":"in my view, as a biologist,"},{"time":752000,"text":"have no reason to be controversial."},{"time":754000,"text":"My fellow environmentalists, on this subject,"},{"time":756000,"text":"have been irrational, anti-scientific, and very harmful."},{"time":760000,"text":"Despite their best efforts,"},{"time":762000,"text":"genetically engineered crops are the most"},{"time":764000,"text":"rapidly successful agricultural innovation in history."},{"time":768000,"text":"They're good for the environment because they enable no-till farming,"},{"time":771000,"text":"which leaves the soil in place,"},{"time":773000,"text":"getting healthier from year to year --"},{"time":775000,"text":"slso keeps less carbon dioxide going from the soil"},{"time":777000,"text":"into the atmosphere."},{"time":779000,"text":"They reduce pesticide use."},{"time":781000,"text":"And they increase yield, which allows you to have your"},{"time":783000,"text":"agricultural area be smaller,"},{"time":786000,"text":"and therefore more wild area is freed up."}]},{"cues":[{"time":789000,"text":"By the way, this map from 2006"},{"time":791000,"text":"is out of date because it shows Africa"},{"time":793000,"text":"still under the thumb of Greenpeace,"},{"time":795000,"text":"and Friends of the Earth from Europe,"},{"time":798000,"text":"and they're finally getting out from under that."},{"time":800000,"text":"And biotech is moving rapidly in Africa, at last."}]},{"cues":[{"time":803000,"text":"This is a moral issue."},{"time":805000,"text":"The Nuffield Council on Bioethics"},{"time":807000,"text":"met on this issue twice in great detail"},{"time":809000,"text":"and said it is a moral imperative"},{"time":811000,"text":"to make genetically engineered crops readily available."},{"time":814000,"text":"Speaking of imperatives, geoengineering is taboo now,"},{"time":817000,"text":"especially in government circles,"},{"time":819000,"text":"though I think there was a DARPA meeting on it a couple of weeks ago,"},{"time":821000,"text":"but it will be on your plate --"},{"time":823000,"text":"not this year but pretty soon,"},{"time":826000,"text":"because some harsh realizations are coming along."},{"time":829000,"text":"This is a list of them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":831000,"text":"Basically the news is going to keep getting more scary."},{"time":834000,"text":"There will be events,"},{"time":836000,"text":"like 35,000 people dying of a heat wave,"},{"time":839000,"text":"which happened a while back."},{"time":841000,"text":"Like cyclones coming up toward Bangladesh."},{"time":844000,"text":"Like wars over water,"},{"time":846000,"text":"such as in the Indus."},{"time":848000,"text":"And as those events keep happening"},{"time":850000,"text":"we're going to say, \"Okay, what can we do about that really?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":852000,"text":"But there's this little problem with geoengineering:"},{"time":857000,"text":"what body is going to decide"},{"time":861000,"text":"who gets to engineer? How much they do? Where they do it?"},{"time":863000,"text":"Because everybody is downstream,"},{"time":865000,"text":"downwind of whatever is done."},{"time":868000,"text":"And if we just taboo it completely"},{"time":870000,"text":"we could lose civilization."},{"time":872000,"text":"But if we just say \"OK,"},{"time":875000,"text":"China, you're worried, you go ahead."},{"time":877000,"text":"You geoengineer your way. We'll geoengineer our way.\""},{"time":881000,"text":"That would be considered an act of war by both nations."},{"time":884000,"text":"So this is very interesting diplomacy coming along."},{"time":888000,"text":"I should say, it is more practical than people think."}]},{"cues":[{"time":891000,"text":"Here is an example that climatologists like a lot,"},{"time":894000,"text":"one of the dozens of geoengineering ideas."},{"time":896000,"text":"This one came from the sulfur dioxide"},{"time":898000,"text":"from Mount Pinatubo in 1991 --"},{"time":901000,"text":"cooled the earth by half a degree."},{"time":905000,"text":"There was so much ice in 1992, the following year,"},{"time":907000,"text":"that there was a bumper crop of polar bear cubs"},{"time":910000,"text":"who were known as the Pinatubo cubs."},{"time":912000,"text":"To put sulfur dioxide in the stratosphere"},{"time":914000,"text":"would cost on the order of a billion dollars a year."},{"time":917000,"text":"That's nothing, compared to all of the other"},{"time":920000,"text":"things we may be trying to do about energy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":922000,"text":"Just to run by another one:"},{"time":925000,"text":"this is a plan to brighten the reflectance of ocean clouds,"},{"time":928000,"text":"by atomizing seawater;"},{"time":930000,"text":"that would brighten the albedo of the whole planet."},{"time":932000,"text":"A nice one, because it can happen"},{"time":934000,"text":"lots of little ways in lots of little places,"},{"time":936000,"text":"is by copying the ancient Amazon Indians"},{"time":938000,"text":"who made good agricultural soil"},{"time":940000,"text":"by pyrolizing, smoldering, plant waste,"},{"time":944000,"text":"and biochar fixes large quantities of carbon"},{"time":947000,"text":"while it's improving the soil."}]},{"cues":[{"time":949000,"text":"So here is where we are."},{"time":952000,"text":"Nobel Prize-winning climatologist Paul Crutzen"},{"time":955000,"text":"calls our geological era the Anthropocene,"},{"time":958000,"text":"the human-dominated era. We are stuck"},{"time":961000,"text":"with its obligations."},{"time":964000,"text":"In the Whole Earth Catalog, my first words were,"},{"time":966000,"text":"\"We are as Gods, and might as well get good at it.\""},{"time":968000,"text":"The first words of Whole Earth Discipline"},{"time":971000,"text":"are, \"We are as Gods, and have to get good at it.\""},{"time":975000,"text":"Thank you."},{"time":977000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}